Create Response Handler, used only for Invoke.

Parameters:
invoke - the invoke activity to receive the message
context - execution context of the invoke activity
portType - the WSDL PortType that declares the operation
style - "rpc" or "document"
operation - Operation BINDING QName - that is, the operations name and the namespace specified in the binding.

The fault message MUST have a single part. The use, encodingStyle and namespace attributes are all used in the same way as with soap:body (see section 3.5), only style="document" is assumed since faults do not contain parameters. [WSDL 3.6]
